data.title: Palm Desert, CA
data.text:
The primary goal of the Palm Desert Chapter is to allow alumni, parents, and friends of Gonzaga to network and further the mission of Gonzaga University in the area through game watches, regional events and service projects. Alumni, family and friends are always welcome at any of our chapter events. We hope to see you at our next event!

Join the Palm Desert Chapter

Chapters are for all Gonzaga alumni, current and former parents, and friends of Gonzaga. There are no fees or dues — it's free!

Chapter Leadership

Paul Storwick was born and raised as a proud Calgarian. Paul is the President of GreatWest Kenworth Ltd. It is a third generation family business that has grown substantially from the early 70’s. Paul graduated with a business degree from Gonzaga University. Currently he is serving his second term as an Honorary Colonel of the RCAF. Paul’s daughter Kat also graduated from GU in 2012. Paul has numerous hobbies and sports including playing hockey, badminton and golf; bird hunting, fishing and skiing as well as woodworking, photography, and plastic model building.
